[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA critical security issue has been detected during fuzz testing of the HTML parsing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponent. The fuzzer triggers an OS Command Injection vulnerability, as evidenced [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby a `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception. [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAttacker-controlled input flows through the Apache Tika parsing chain and [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39multimately reaches a call to `Runtime.exec`, allowing potential remote code [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Identification  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The fuzzer run produces an exception indicating a **FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOS Command Injection**. The stack trace shows that untrusted data reaches a call to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ProcessBuilder.start` and `Runtime.exec`.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  This is an **OS Command Injection** vulnerability, where malicious input can [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malter or inject shell commands, leading to unauthorized execution of system [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcommands.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key Observations  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The crash originates in the `OsCommandInjection.processImplStartHook` of the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJazzer sanitizer, which flags the insecure command invocation.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The offending calls are `[0m[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1;39m([0m[39mProcessBuilder.jav[0m[1;92ma:1110[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mRuntime.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRuntime.jav[0m[1;92ma:594[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m453[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The attack surface is within the Apache Tika parsing pipeline, specifically the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ExternalParser.parse` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m274[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m314[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which spawns external processes.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The HTML parsing stack includes:  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – `ParserDecorator` → `CompositeParser` → `AutoDetectParser` → [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`DelegatingParser` → `ParsingEmbeddedDocumentExtractor` → `HtmlHandler` → [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`XHTMLDowngradeHandler` → `JSoupParser` → back into `CompositeParser`.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness entry points are in `com.example.HtmlParserFuzzer`:  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – `parseOne` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m69[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m invokes the Tika parser.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – `fuzzerTestOneInput` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m feeds fuzzed input into `parseOne`.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Areas for Investigation  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. **ExternalParser Implementation**: Review how command-line invocations are [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructed and whether input is sanitized or parameterized.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. **Command Invocation Sites**: Locate all usages of `Runtime.exec` and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ProcessBuilder` within the Tika codebase.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. **Parser Data Flow**: Trace how HTML content, data URIs, or embedded documents[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare passed from the fuzzer harness through `HtmlHandler` and `JSoupParser` to the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexternal parser.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. **Fuzzer Harness**: Understand the kinds of inputs generated by [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`HtmlParserFuzzer` that trigger this path, to reproduce and analyze the exact [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpayload that leads to command injection.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35mcom.example.HtmlParserFuzzer.parseOne[0m[1;39m([0m[39mHtmlParserFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:69[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.HtmlParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mHtmlParserFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:40[0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: 3c99eeb1380e104c[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a Jazzer-detected OS Command Injection in Apache Tika’s [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExternalParser class. Untrusted input passed to `Runtime.exec` or [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ProcessBuilder.start` can lead to remote code execution.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch was proposed that replaces direct calls to `[0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.exec` with[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma loop applying a hypothetical [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.process.ProcessUtils.escapeCommandLine` method to each command [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtoken, then invokes `ProcessBuilder` on the escaped tokens.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhen building after applying the patch, the compiler fails because [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.process.ProcessUtils` does not exist in the codebase, resulting in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma missing-package error and a failed compilation of tika-core.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A critical FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical exception was raised for OS command [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minjection.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack trace shows ExternalParser invoking `Runtime.exec` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ProcessBuilder.start`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m on attacker-controlled data.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The vulnerability arises when HTML is parsed and embedded data URIs trigger [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexternal parsing commands built from unescaped input.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations from the Initial Issue  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - ExternalParser builds a `String[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m cmd` array representing the external command[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand its arguments.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Both single-string and multi-element overloads of `Runtime.exec` are used.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No sanitization or escaping is applied to the elements of `cmd`.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`HtmlParserFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m supplies inputs that flow through [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTika’s parser chain into ExternalParser.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt Details  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Patch location: [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/external/ExternalParser.java`, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maround line [0m[1;36m308[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Original code:  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • If `cmd.length == [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`, call `[0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Else call `[0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replacement code:  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Construct `String[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m safeCmd` of same length as `cmd`.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Loop over each `cmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, assign `safeCmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mProcessUtils.escapeCommandLine[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Create `ProcessBuilder pb = new [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39msafeCmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Start process via `[0m[1;35mpb.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result and Build Failure  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compilation error: `package org.apache.tika.process does not exist` at [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExternalParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:314[0m[39m.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The reference to `org.apache.tika.process.ProcessUtils` cannot be resolved.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The tika-core module fails to compile; all downstream modules are skipped.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify whether a command-escaping utility [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ProcessUtils` or similar[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m exists [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min another module or needs to be created.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inspect the module layout to locate any existing process-helper classes or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpackages. Possible locations:  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • A separate “process” or “utils” package under tika-core or a sibling module.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The tika-commandline or tika-process contributions [0m[1;39m([0m[39mif any[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review ExternalParser’s construction of `cmd` to understand all input sources [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mHTML handlers, embedded extractors[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Examine build configuration [0m[1;39m([0m[39mMaven POMs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to see if a dependency on a [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocess-escaping library is missing.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo root‐cause speculation or remediation strategies are provided here. This report [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcaptures the issue, the attempted fix, and the observed compilation outcome.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m312[0m[39m:                process = [0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m313[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m314[0m[39m:                process = [0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo resolve the compilation failure and eliminate the OS‐command‐injection in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExternalParser, we will mirror the proven pattern from [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`parser.external2.ExternalParser`, reusing the existing [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.utils.ProcessUtils` utility, rather than referencing a [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnon‐existent `org.apache.tika.process` package. Our patch must satisfy three goals:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Remove all direct calls to `[0m[1;35mRuntime.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, replacing them with a secured [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` invocation.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Properly escape every command token using `[0m[1;35mProcessUtils.escapeCommandLine[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto neutralize injections [0m[1;39m([0m[39mespecially on Windows[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Preserve ExternalParser’s existing logic for feeding STDIN, reading [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSTDOUT/STDERR, enforcing timeouts, and cleaning up child processes.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSteps:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Add the missing import at the top of `ExternalParser.java`:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     import org.apache.tika.utils.ProcessUtils;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Locate the block around line [0m[1;36m309[0m[39m that currently reads:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd.length == [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         process = [0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         process = [0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Replace it with a single‐branch that:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Allocates a `String[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m safeCmd = new String[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcmd.length[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Fills each entry via `safeCmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[1;35mProcessUtils.escapeCommandLine[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Constructs `ProcessBuilder pb = new [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39msafeCmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Calls `process = [0m[1;35mpb.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This removes both unsafe `Runtime.exec` overloads.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Ensure we continue to use the existing code that handles:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If `inputToStdIn` is true, copy the input stream into [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mprocess.getOutputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If `outputFromStdOut` is true, read from `[0m[1;35mprocess.getInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and emit [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mXHTML.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If `outputFromStdOut` is false, read from the temporary output file.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Read and apply the metadata patterns to `[0m[1;35mprocess.getErrorStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Enforce timeouts [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`waitFor`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and forcibly destroy the process on interrupt or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Log any exception via `[0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"problem with process exec"[0m[39m, e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. No other import changes or dependency additions are required—`ProcessUtils` sits[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `tika-core` already under `org.apache.tika.utils`.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Compilation Fix**: By importing the correct package [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`org.apache.tika.utils.ProcessUtils`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, we eliminate the “package … does not exist”[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merror.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Security**: Token-by-token escaping plus `[0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` ensures [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meach element is passed as a discrete argument, preventing shell‐style [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconcatenation.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Preservation**: We preserve all existing ExternalParser behaviors—input [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstreaming, output parsing, metadata extraction, timeouts, and resource cleanup—by [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly altering the process‐launch snippet.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Consistency**: This fix aligns ExternalParser with its sibling [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`parser.external2.ExternalParser`, reducing future maintenance friction.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPotential Side Effects and Mitigations:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Windows behavior**: `ProcessUtils.escapeCommandLine` only adds quotes on [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWindows when spaces are detected. On Unix, quoting is unnecessary. Our use of [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ProcessBuilder` sidesteps shell interpretation entirely.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Argument Splitting**: As before, the code splits a single‐element command [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstring on whitespace [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35m.split[0m[1;39m([0m[32m" "[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. If callers require more advanced parsing [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g., escaped spaces[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, they should already supply an array. Our patch does not [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchange that behavior.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Performance**: The small per‐token loop and creation of a `ProcessBuilder` have[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnegligible performance impact compared to process startup overhead.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo modifications to fuzz harnesses, tests, or utility code beyond adding one import[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand rewriting the exec block are needed.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>tika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/external/ExternalParser.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjav[0m[1;92ma:17[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m24[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>tika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/external/ExternalParser.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjav[0m[1;92ma:309[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m315[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer identified a critical OS command injection issue in [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ExternalParser.parse`, where attacker-controlled data was passed to `Runtime.exec`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mand indirectly to `ProcessBuilder.start`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. A patch replaced the direct [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Runtime.exec` calls with a `ProcessBuilder` that wraps each command token using [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ProcessUtils.escapeCommandLine`. After applying this change, the fuzzer still [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggers the same `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: OS Command Injection` on [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ProcessBuilder.start`, indicating that the patch did not eliminate the sanitizer’s[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfinding.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Exception thrown:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: OS Command [0m      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     at [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.OsCommandInjection.processImplStartHook[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     at [0m[1;35mjava.lang.ProcessBuilder.start[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     at [0m[1;35mjava.lang.Runtime.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     at [0m[1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.external.ExternalParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Context: The Tika `ExternalParser` class constructs a shell command array [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`cmd` and invokes `[0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.exec` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwith either a single string or a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstring array[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to execute external utilities. The fuzzer’s sanitizer hook detected [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat these command arguments are derived from untrusted input, raising a critical [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity alert.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash stack points to `ExternalParser.parse` lines [0m[1;36m314[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m275[0m[39m in the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginal code.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Both overloads of `Runtime.exec` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstring and string-array[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m were used, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdepending on `cmd.length`.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The Tika parsing chain [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCompositeParser, AutoDetectParser, DelegatingParser[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunnels data into `ExternalParser.parse`, making it reachable by arbitrary fuzzer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minputs.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added import: `import org.apache.tika.utils.ProcessUtils;`  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replaced the two `[0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` invocations with:  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • A loop that applies `[0m[1;35mProcessUtils.escapeCommandLine[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to each token. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Construction of a `ProcessBuilder` using the escaped tokens.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `process = [0m[1;35mpb.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` in place of `Runtime.exec`.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch diff [0m[1;39m([0m[39msimplified[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + String[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m safeCmd = new String[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcmd.length[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint i = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < cmd.length; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m293[0m[39m:            cmd = new String[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcommand.length[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m294[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mSystem.arraycopy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommand, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, cmd, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, command.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m295[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m296[0m[39m:        for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint i = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < cmd.length; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/external/ExternalParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:309[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m315[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m309[0m[39m:        Process process = null;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m310[0m[39m:        try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m311[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd.length == [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m312[0m[39m:                process = [0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m313[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m314[0m[39m:                process = [0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m315[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/utils/ProcessUtils.jav[0m[1;92ma:56[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m67[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m56[0m[39m:    public static String [0m[1;35mescapeCommandLine[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString arg[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m57[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39marg == null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[39m:            return arg;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m59[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95mneed[0m[39m to test for [0m[32m" "[0m[39m on windows, can't just add double quotes[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m61[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95macross[0m[39m platforms.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35marg.contains[0m[1;39m([0m[32m" "[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && SystemUtils.IS_OS_WINDOWS &&[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m63[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35marg.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"\""[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && ![0m[1;35marg.endsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"\""[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m:            arg = [0m[32m"\""[0m[39m + arg + [0m[32m"\""[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m:        return arg;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/external2/ExternalParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:128[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m13[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m128[0m[39m:            long localTimeoutMillis = [0m[1;35mTikaTaskTimeout.getTimeoutMillis[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeoutMs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m129[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moutputFileInCommandline[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m130[0m[39m:                result = [0m[1;35mProcessUtils.execute[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnew [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mthisCommandLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m131[0m[39m:                        localTimeoutMillis, maxStdOut, maxStdErr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m132[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m133[0m[39m:                outFile = [0m[1;35mFiles.createTempFile[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"tika-external2-"[0m[39m, [0m[32m""[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m134[0m[39m:                result = [0m[1;35mProcessUtils.execute[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnew [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mthisCommandLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m135[0m[39m:                        localTimeoutMillis, outFile, maxStdErr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m136[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The Jazzer sanitizer flags any `[0m[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` invocation on [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“untrusted” data—escaping via `ProcessUtils.escapeCommandLine` does not actually [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitize Unix-style meta-characters and does nothing on non-Windows platforms, so [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mpb.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` remains vulnerable in the sanitizer’s eyes.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Splitting a single‐element `command[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` on spaces back into tokens [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35m.split[0m[1;39m([0m[32m" [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m can also introduce unvalidated fragments.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The sanitizer does not track whether tokens have been escaped or [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhitelisted—it sees any non-constant data flowing into `[0m[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` as [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munsafe.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy Overview[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Eliminate any path where attacker-influenced content reaches [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Introduce a strict validation/whitelist of allowed command tokens before [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvoking an external process.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Remove the fallback case that splits a single string on spaces.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Preserve existing functionality [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexternal parser support[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for known binaries [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile ensuring that no untrusted payload ever reaches the OS.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   E. Do not modify harness, fuzzing logic, or tests.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Steps[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Centralize command token validation[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Create a method in `ExternalParser` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor a shared utility[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m called [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mvalidateExternalCommandToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString token[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Enforce a whitelist of allowed characters: `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mA-Za-z0-9_.[0m[35m/[0m[39m\\-[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Explicitly reject tokens containing any of `;`, `|`, `&`, `` ` ``, `$`, `<`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`>`, `\n`, or other shell-meta characters.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • For extra safety, enforce a maximum token length [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m[1;36m256[0m[39m chars[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • If validation fails, throw a `TikaException` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor a dedicated checked [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m indicating “Invalid external command token”.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Prevent splitting on spaces[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Change the logic at lines [0m[1;36m289[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m296[0m[39m to no longer do `command[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;35m.split[0m[1;39m([0m[32m" "[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Always treat the configured `command[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` array as the definitive list of [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtokens. This avoids accidental tokenization of attacker-controlled strings.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Replace:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommand.length == [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           cmd = command[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;35m.split[0m[1;39m([0m[32m" "[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       With:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         cmd = new String[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcommand.length[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mSystem.arraycopy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommand, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, cmd, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, command.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Step [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: Validate every token before execution[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Immediately after building `cmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, iterate:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mString token : cmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mvalidateExternalCommandToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtoken[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     This guarantees that by the time you reach the `ProcessBuilder` invocation, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnone of the tokens can contain injection vectors.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Step [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m: Execute the external process with ProcessBuilder[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - With tokens validated, you can safely do:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ProcessBuilder pb = new [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       Process process = [0m[1;35mpb.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Retain all existing I/O redirection, timeout handling, and cleanup logic.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whitelisting removes any possibility that semicolons, pipes, or other [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshell-meta characters slip through—even on Unix platforms.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By forbidding splitting, we avoid creating unintended sub-tokens from user [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We preserve the core functionality [0m[1;39m([0m[39msupport for external parsers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting test suite.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The sanitizer will see that the same tokens are always drawn from static [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfig [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand validated[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so injection risk is eliminated—even if the sanitizer still[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflags any `[0m[1;35mstart[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, it will no longer consider the data untrusted.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes are made to harness, fuzz framework, or third-party libraries.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigation[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If a user’s TikaConfig specified a command token containing a space or an [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munusual character [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., “[0m[35m/usr/bin/[0m[95mmy-tool[0m[39m v2”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, validation will now reject it.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Mitigation: Document the new restriction—commands must be pre-tokenized in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTikaConfig. Provide guidance on how to split multi-word commands into array form.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Very long tokens [0m[1;39m([0m[39m>[0m[1;36m256[0m[39m chars[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are rejected. This is unlikely for executable [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnames or flags. If required, the length limit can be raised in a future release.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Reference[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar approach in other parts of Tika where external processes are invoked [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g., code in the `external2` parser[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, adopting the same token validation method [0m  [2m                [0m
